IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: IMPROVE THE HEALTH & WELL-BEING OF UNDER- served populations by providing gov't purchased prepaid healthcare coverage to individuals covered under medicaid and other health progs.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO IMPROVE THE HEALTH AND WELL-BEING OF UNDERSERVED POPULATIONS BY PROVIDING COMPREHENSIVE PREPAID HEALTHCARE COVERAGE TO MEDICAID, MANAGED LONG TERM CARE (MLTC), ESSENTIAL PLAN, HARP, QUALIFIED HEALTH PLAN AND CHILD HEALTH PLUS RECIPIENTS.
IRS990.Desc: MEDICAID MANAGED CARE: HEALTHFIRST PHSP, INC. (PHSP) IS A LICENSED PREPAID HEALTH SERVICES PLAN THAT PROVIDES COMPREHENSIVE PREPAID HEALTH CARE COVERAGE TO BENEFICIARIES OF GOVERNMENT HEALTH CARE COVERAGE PROGRAMS. PHSP HAS PARTICIPATED IN NEW YORK'S MEDICAID PROGRAM SINCE OCTOBER 1994. FOR 2019 THERE WERE 1,200,456 MEMBERS ENROLLED IN PHSP'S MEDICAID PLAN.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: MANAGED LONG TERM CARE (MLTC) SERVICES SUCH AS PERSONAL CARE, SOCIAL, NUTRITIONAL AND REHABILITATION SERVICES WERE PROVIDED TO OVER 19,113 FRAIL ELDERLY INDIVIDUALS RESIDING IN MANHATTAN, THE BRONX, BROOKLYN, QUEENS, STATEN ISLAND, NASSAU AND WESTCHESTER DURING 2019, ALLOWING THEM TO CONTINUE TO RESIDE SAFELY WITHIN THEIR COMMUNITY.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: ESSENTIAL PLAN (EP): HEALTHFIRST PHSP, INC. (PHSP) IS A LICENSED PREPAID HEALTH SERVICES PLAN THAT PROVIDES COMPREHENSIVE PREPAID HEALTH CARE COVERAGE TO BENEFICIARIES OF GOVERNMENT HEALTH CARE COVERAGE PROGRAMS. EP IS A PROGRAM WHICH COVERS INDIVIDUALS WHO WOULD OTHERWISE BE ELIGIBLE FOR EITHER CERTAIN CATEGORIES OF EXPANDED MEDICAID COVERAGE OR SIGNIFICANT SUBSIDIES FOR QUALIFIED HEALTH PLAN (QHP) FOR LITTLE OR NO MEMBER CONTRIBUTION. FOR 2019 THERE WERE 259,788 MEMBERS ENROLLED IN PHSP'S EP PLAN.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART III, LINE 4D OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: HEALTH AND RECOVERY PLAN (HARP): HEALTHFIRST PHSP, INC. (PHSP) IS A LICENSED PREPAID HEALTH SERVICES PLAN THAT PROVIDES COMPREHENSIVE PREPAID HEALTH CARE COVERAGE TO MEDICAID ELIGIBLE INDIVIDUALS THAT HAVE SERIOUS BEHAVIORAL HEALTH DIAGNOSES. THE HARP PROGRAM WAS INTRODUCED IN 2015 AND IS A MANAGED CARE PROGRAM WITHIN MEDICAID. Qualified Health Plans (QHP): In 2014, PHSP established a Qualified Health Plan ("QHP") under the Health Care Reform, which is certified by the New York State Health Insurance Marketplace ("Marketplace"). QHP provides essential health benefits, follows established limits on cost-sharing (deductible, copayment, and out-of-pocket maximum amounts), and must maintain compliance with other provisions of Health Care Reform. QHP is administered under an agreement between PHSP and the DOH that extends through December 31, 2023. CHILD HEALTH PLUS (CHP): THE ORGANIZATION IS A LICENSED PREPAID HEALTH SERVICES PLAN THAT PROVIDES COMPREHENSIVE PREPAID HEALTH CARE COVERAGE TO CHP RECIPIENTS PURSUANT TO ARTICLE 44 OF THE NEW YORK STATE PUBLIC HEALTH LAW. PHSP HAS PARTICIPATED IN NEW YORK'S CHP PROGRAM SINCE 1997. BASIC HEALTH PLANS (BHP): HEALTHFIRST PHSP, INC. (PHSP) IS A LICENSED PREPAID HEALTH SERVICES PLAN THAT PROVIDES STANDARD HEALTH PLAN COVERAGE TO ELIGIBLE INDIVIDUALS WHO WOULD NOT HAVE ACCESS TO COVERAGE THROUGH THE HEALTH INSURANCE MARKETPLACE. PHSP UNDERTOOK NEW YORK'S BHP PROGRAM AS OF 2015. FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 3 HEALTHFIRST PHSP, INC. (PHSP) CONTRACTS WITH HF MANAGEMENT SERVICES, LLC (HFMS) TO PROVIDE ALL OF ITS MANAGEMENT AND ADMINISTRATIVE SERVICES. PHSP DOES NOT MAINTAIN ITS OWN STAFF OR OFFICE SPACE; THESE ARE PROVIDED BY HFMS. HFMS CHARGES A PERCENT OF PREMIUM ON A PER MEMBER PER MONTH BASIS OR A FLAT FEE PER MEMBER PER MONTH. THE ARRANGEMENT IS APPROVED BY RESOLUTION OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND THE NY STATE DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH. ALL OFFICERS, KEY EMPLOYEES, AND HIGHEST COMPENSATED EMPLOYEES WERE PAID BY, AND WORKED FOR HFMS, A MANAGEMENT COMPANY WHICH PROVIDES MANAGEMENT SERVICES FOR MULTIPLE ENTITIES. NONE OF THE INDIVIDUALS LISTED EARNED ANY COMPENSATION FROM PHSP. ALL OFFICERS, KEY EMPLOYEES, AND HIGHEST COMPENSATED EMPLOYEES WERE PAID BY, AND WORKED FOR HFMS, A MANAGEMENT COMPANY WHICH PROVIDES MANAGEMENT SERVICES FOR MULTIPLE ENTITIES. NONE OF THE INDIVIDUALS LISTED EARNED ANY COMPENSATION FROM PHSP.

In July 2018, we started processing some of our payments to provider via by card. These payments are reported on 1099K by the provider's merchant service. In 2019, the number of 1099s issued by HEALTHFIRST PHSP, INC. was reduced significantly since it was the first full year processing card payments from merchant service (VPay). FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6 Healthfirst, Inc. has the right to appoint the members of the Board of Directors of HEALTHFIRST.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE 990 IS PREPARED BY THE HF MANAGEMENT SERVICES, LLC (HFMS) CORPORATE FINANCE DEPARTMENT STAFF AND THEN REVIEWED BY THE HFMS VICE PRESIDENT, CONTROLLER. SECONDARY REVIEWS ARE ALSO PERFORMED BY THE HFMS CHIEF LEGAL OFFICER AND CHIEF FINANCIAL OFFICER. THE DRAFT 990 IS THEN REVIEWED BY AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTING FIRM. THE DRAFT 990 IS THEN PRESENTED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS FOR REVIEW. THE FINAL 990 IS SUBMITTED AFTER THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS REVIEWS IT.
